@@TJvLabelAppear
Summary
  Enables the label to fly onto the form.
Description
  Use TJvLabelAppear to enable a TJvBehaviorLabel to fly onto the form. The label can be set to appear
  from the top, right, bottom or left side of the screen. The appearing sequence is handled in a
  background thread which makes it possible to have multiple labels appearing at the same time.

  When the label has appeared, the OnAppeared event is called.

  To use TJvLabelAppear capabilities with a TJvBehaviorLabel label, do the following:

  * Drop a TJvBehaviorLabel on a form.
  * Set <LINK TJvCustomBehaviorLabel.Behavior, Behavior> to 'Appearing'.

  Do the following with the properties of property <LINK TJvCustomBehaviorLabel.BehaviorOptions,
  BehaviorOptions>:

  * Use AppearFrom to specify the direction from which the label is to appear.
  * Set Delay to an interval in milliseconds before the label starts appearing.
  * Set Interval to an interval in milliseconds between two moves of the label.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvLabelAppear.AppearFrom
Summary
  Indicates the direction from which the label is to appear.
Description
  AppearFrom indicates the direction from which the label appears on the form. You can specify if the
  should appear from the left (drFromLeft), the right (drFromRight), the top (drFromTop) or the bottom
  (drFromBottom) of the form.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvLabelAppear.Delay
Summary
  The interval before the label starts appearing.
Description
  Delay determines the initial delay (in milliseconds) before the label begins to move into view.
See Also
  TJvLabelAppear.Interval

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvLabelAppear.Interval
Summary
  The interval between two moves of the label.
Description
  Interval indicates the delay (in milliseconds) between two stages of appearing.

  Interval determines how frequently the scroll event occurs. Each time the specified interval passes,
  the label text scrolls.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvLabelAppear.Pixels
Summary
  Number of pixels to move.
Description
  Pixels indicates the number of pixels to move every interval.
See Also
  TJvLabelAppear.Interval

