@@TJvLabelBounce
Summary
  Enables the label to bounce.
Description
  TJvLabelBounce enables a TJvBehaviorLabel to bounce on the form.

  To use TJvLabelBounce capabilities with a TJvBehaviorLabel label, do the following:

  * Drop a TJvBehaviorLabel on a form.
  * Set <LINK TJvCustomBehaviorLabel.Behavior, Behavior> to 'Bouncing'.

  Do the following with the properties of property <LINK TJvCustomBehaviorLabel.BehaviorOptions,
  BehaviorOptions>:

  * Use Interval to specify the amount of time in milliseconds between scroll events.
  * Use Direction to change the default scroll direction.
  * Set Active to True at design-time, or set this property at run-time to start the bouncing.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvLabelBounce.Interval
Summary
  Specifies how often the label is moved.
Description
  Use Interval to set the number of milliseconds between moves of the label. Interval works in
  conjuction with Pixels to define how fast and smoothly the label moves.
See Also
  Pixels

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvLabelBounce.Pixels
Summary
  Specifies the number of pixels the label moves at each update.
Description
  Use Pixels to set how far the label moves at each update. The time between updates is controlled by
  the Interval property. Setting Pixels to a high value will make the label move in larger steps.
See Also
  TJvLabelBounce.Interval

